Cactus Code Thorn KerrQuasiIsotropic
Author(s)    : Helvi Witek
Maintainer(s): Helvi Witek
Licence      : GPLv2+
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Purpose
===========
KerrQuasiIsotropic provides analytic initial data for a rotating black hole, spinning around the z-axis, in quasi-isotropic coordinates 
$r_{\rm BL} = R \left( 1 + \frac{r_{\rm BL,+}}{4 R}\right)^{2}$.
We employ the construction of Liu et al, with our specific construction outlined in Eqs.(46)-(48) of Okawa et al.

2. Applications
================
This thorn has been used 
- as basis of the thorn "Proca/TwoPunctures_KerrProca" 
  Note: for long-term stable evolutions of highly spinning black holes, we recommend a modified puncture gauge 
  (see Witek \& Zilh\~{a}o, in progress)
  that is available in the new_gauge branch of LeanBSSNMoL.
- to study the evolution of massive scalar/vector fields in rotating BH backgrounds
- to explore the evolution of the dilaton in Einstein-dilaton Gauss--Bonnet gravity


3. References 
==============
- Liu et al; https://arxiv.org/abs/1001.4077
- Okawa et al; https://arxiv.org/abs/1401.1548

see also:
- Witek \& Zilh\~{a}o; in progress
- https://arxiv.org/abs/1810.05177

